            "comments": [
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Geissler",
                        "email": "geissonator@yahoo.com",
                        "username": "geissonator"
                    },
                    "message": "There appears to be a lot of copy/paste between this and the other design. I recommend just starting a discussion on your alternative in that reviews \"Alternatives Considered\" section of the other review."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Medicine Yeh",
                        "email": "medicinehy@gmail.com",
                        "username": "MedicineYeh"
                    },
                    "message": "In addition to the design, I also updated the requirements and problem description so that the story is more consistent. Michael has concerns that this new requirements will not be taken by upstream so I started a new one. To make it easier to read, I removed the common parts in this change and keep only the parts that needs to be reviewed.\n\nFrom the implementation perspective, the main difference is that this design focuses on recording actual events instead of predefining a table. Thus, no need to maintain the state machine transition table."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Medicine Yeh",
                        "email": "medicinehy@gmail.com",
                        "username": "MedicineYeh"
                    },
                    "message": "Gentle ping for review."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Jeffery",
                        "email": "andrew@aj.id.au",
                        "username": "amboar"
                    },
                    "message": "I think you'll get better traction if you follow Andrew G's request and work to enhance the other proposal. Your aim is to develop consensus in the community, not divide community efforts."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 12,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Medicine Yeh",
                        "email": "medicinehy@gmail.com",
                        "username": "MedicineYeh"
                    },
                    "message": "Thanks for the advice. Michael will merge this to his design doc."
                }
